<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-03-31T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-03-31T18:00:00-05:00" n="299" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d299">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00 Nanking/247: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Cunningham</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-03-31T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">March 31,
                                        1928—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>For the Minister. Department’s March 31, 1 p.m., your March 31, 8 p.m.
                            Notes which you have signed are satisfactory. Department has no further
                            comments to make.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>